<br>
We set off from Surefall Glade with 40+ brave marchers, ranging in levels from 1 to 42. Our trek took us through all the Karana regions, Lake Rathe and the Rathe Mountains, the Gorge, Misty Thicket, Rivervale, Kithicor Woods, The Commonlands and on into Freeport. Amazing sights and sharp skirmishes marked our passage. A Griffon fell beneath the weight of a mass attack in North Karana, and a Hill Giant met a similar fate in the Rathe Mountains. A raging band of minotaurs were dealt with in the Gorge, and the Goblin King himself tried to stop our march through Runnyeye, only to find himself laying face down on the floor of his own dark caverns. Two first level adventurers were slain during the walk (one of them twice) but both were recovered and marched proudly into Freeport with us.<br>
<br>
We lingered a few minutes in Rivervale, where the loot off the Goblin King was awarded via lotto. Congratulations to Olenka, who won a Blackened Iron Medallion, and Rezzaenia, who won a Blackened Iron Girdle! In addition, every marcher level 10 and below was awarded a prize courtesy of Haemish MacLennan and the Silver Daggers!<br>
<br>
Further congratulations are due Olenka, who we believe to be the only level 1 adventurer ever to WALK (not run) completely across the continent unscathed! Well done, Olenka, and well done to everyone who made part or all of the trek with us! I will be forever honored to tell the tale of leading such a fine band on this adventure!<br>
<br>
Many thanks are due the Silver Daggers, the Dark Oracles, Cold Comfort and the Karana Council of Guilds for helping to make this the hugely entertaining event that it was. Special thanks to Haemish, Eleysian, Belce, Zoboomafu, Samadani, Milquetoast and Cassia for all your hard work!<br>
<br>
Based on the success of this event, we are planning future walks!<br>
<br>
If anyone would like to organize a similar event, I'll be glad to share ideas and lessons learned. Email me at doged2@mindspring.com .<br>
<br>
Well done, Walkers, and see you all in Norrath!<br>
